The paper deals with the analysis of a multiple-input single-output (MISO) broadcast channel (BC) with imperfect channel state information (CSI) for each user. This topic falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the Degrees of Freedom (DoF) region, which is a concept in wireless communication and networking, making the paper relevant to the signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. Finally, the paper also discusses outer bounds and achievability, which are concepts in coding theory and error-correcting codes, making the paper relevant to the computer engineering (cs.CE) category.
